<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Refund and Dispute Policy - FixMyHome</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;700&family=Source+Sans+3:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
</head>
<body class="site-body auth-body">
  <div class="auth-theme-toggle">
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-theme-toggle>Dark mode</button>
  </div>
  <main class="auth-shell legal-shell">
    <section class="auth-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">FixMyHome Legal</p>
      <h1>Refund and Dispute Policy</h1>
      <p>This policy describes how escrow funding, payment release, and disputes are handled on the platform.</p>
      <p class="job-meta">Last updated: March 17, 2026</p>
    </section>

    <section class="auth-card app-card legal-card">
      <h2>1. Escrow funding</h2>
      <p>When a homeowner awards a bid, the platform may require escrow funding before work begins. Funds remain held until the work is completed and released or a dispute changes the outcome.</p>

      <h2>2. Release</h2>
      <p>After the homeowner confirms completion, escrowed funds are released to the accepted handyman according to the platform payment flow.</p>

      <h2>3. Disputes</h2>
      <p>Either side may open a dispute while funds are held. During an open dispute, payment release is paused while the issue is reviewed through the platform’s dispute workflow.</p>

      <h2>4. Refunds</h2>
      <p>Refunds may be issued where a dispute is resolved in the homeowner’s favor, where payment processing errors occur, or where required by law or provider policy.</p>

      <h2>5. Support and evidence</h2>
      <p>Users should provide clear messages, photos, receipts, and other relevant evidence to support a dispute or refund review.</p>

      <h2>6. Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about refunds or disputes can be sent to <a href="mailto:<%= supportEmail %>"><%= supportEmail %></a>.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <%- include('partials/site-footer') %>
  <script src="/theme-toggle.js" defer></script>
</body>
</html>
